Have fun Yahshosh.

Ice::
She continued walking.  Her shoulder felt like it was on fire. She 
groaned a bit, but didn't stop. The snow was falling harder now.  She 
looked back behind her and saw the massive paw prints. She 
smiled. "At least I'm not as small as I used to be." She turned and 
kept walking north.  

She looked out and saw a large patch of ice. She tapped the ice with 
her paw. It looked solid enough. She stepped out onto the ice. About 
half way out, she saw fish, trapped in the ice. Her noce picked up on 
the scent and she felt her empty stomach growl a little. She 
scratched at the ice, trying to get to the fish. She managed to pull 
one fish out. But it wasn't even a mouthful.  But it wasn't all that 
bad either. She saw another one and pawed at the ice.  She stopped 
pawing when she heard a loud crack. "Oh no..that doesn't sound to 
good."  She hear another loud crack as the ice under her started to 
give way. She moved just in time and watches the ice fall into the 
water. She sighed and looked at the hole in the ice. She wished she 
had a fishing pole right then. She sighed and kept walking north. She 
just ignore her shoulder and kept walking. Leaving a small trail as 
she walked. The wound wasn't closing, and a small part of the metal 
skeleton could be seen at the joint.
